RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) security integrates retrieval of external knowledge with LLM generation, requiring safeguards against prompt injection, data poisoning, and unauthorized data leakage.

RAG security for AI agents requires strict guardrails that validate and sanitize retrieved documents before they are fed to the language model.
The agent must manage its memory, limiting context length and securely storing any cached retrievals to prevent data leakage.
All retrieval and generation steps should run inside isolated sandboxes to contain potential code execution or prompt‑injection attacks.

